  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Credit and Financial Services: Affordable Agricultural Financing for Resilient Rural Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">to improve productivity, income and resilience through: increased access to affordable finance in support of better marketing linkages, sustainable and climate change-adapted agricultural intensification, skills and enterprise development in agricultural value chains, support for inclusive policy engagement and increased capacity of women and youth to contribute to household resilience.


Increased willingness of financial intermediaries to disburse affordable agricultural production loans to poor smallholder farmers through participation in GIRSAL risk sharing arrangements, suitable product designs and relevant delivery mechanisms.Increased and resilient agricultural productivity, income of smallholder farmers and graduation programming of ultra-poor, through access to affordable financing, capacity building and extension services.</narrative>
  </description>
